meta:
  origin:
    producer: Council of Economic Advisers and National Center for Health Statistics
    title: Percentage of persons without health insurance
    description: For 1978–2015, both the Council of Economic Advisers (CEA) and the National Center for Health Statistics (NCHS) relied on historical data from the National Health Interview Survey (NHIS). For years prior to 1978, the CEA estimated the overall uninsured rate by combining information from the NHIS on trends in private coverage with administrative data on Medicare and Medicaid enrollment during those years.
    citation_full: (i) 1963–2013, Council of Economic Advisers; (ii) 2014–2015, National Center for Health Statistics.
    url_main: https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/docs/longtermhealthinsuranceseriesmethodologyfinal.pdf
